<emphasis id="B96DEA8BFFA3FFC6FC90FC384296E0D1" box="[853,935,950,967]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="483">Jesus 367</emphasis>
(CEPEC); Mun. de Manoel Vitorino, Rod. Man. Vitorino/ Caatingal, Km 4, região de caatinga, 16 February 1979 (fl, fr), 
<emphasis id="B96DEA8BFFA3FFC6FA65FC404294E0E0" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="483">Mattos Silva s.n.</emphasis>
(CEPEC).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3036512FFA3FFC6FCA8FC714405E662" pageId="13" pageNumber="483" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA63699FFA3FFC6FCA8FC7142E0E7E9" blockId="13.[853,1500,159,1396]" pageId="13" pageNumber="483">
<emphasis id="B96DEA8BFFA3FFC6FCA8FC7142F2E702" bold="true" box="[877,963,1023,1044]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="483">Notes—</emphasis>
The species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D1AFFA3FFC6FAE4FB8E4498E702" box="[1313,1449,1023,1045]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="13" pageNumber="483" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="turneroides">
<emphasis id="B96DEA8BFFA3FFC6FAE4FB8E4498E702" box="[1313,1449,1023,1045]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="483">S. turneroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and shares with it notable heteranthery, with the filament of one stamen much longer than the other four. Like 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D1AFFA3FFC6FA8FFBB444E5E758" box="[1354,1492,1081,1103]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="13" pageNumber="483" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="turneroides">
<emphasis id="B96DEA8BFFA3FFC6FA8FFBB444E5E758" box="[1354,1492,1081,1103]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="483">S. turneroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the flowers are only open in the morning and close by midday. 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D1AFFA3FFC6FC7EFBFA45A8E79F" box="[955,1177,1140,1161]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" pageId="13" pageNumber="483" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="evolvuloides">
<emphasis id="B96DEA8BFFA3FFC6FC7EFBFA45A8E79F" box="[955,1177,1140,1161]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="483">Solanum evolvuloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily distinguished from all other species in sect. 
<emphasis id="B96DEA8BFFA3FFC6FB6AFB1F4477E7B0" box="[1199,1350,1169,1190]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="483">Gonatotrichum</emphasis>
by the glandular, multicellular hairs on the stems, inflorescences, and flowers that are not found in any other species of the section.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA63699FFA3FFC6FCA8FA884405E662" blockId="13.[853,1500,159,1396]" pageId="13" pageNumber="483">
<emphasis id="B96DEA8BFFA3FFC6FCA8FA8842D7E60D" box="[877,998,1286,1307]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="483">Jardim 1843</emphasis>
from the banks of the Rio de Contas near the city of Itacaré might be an occasional case of water dispersal by the Contas River, which originates in a xeric environment near the center of Bahia in the caatinga biome.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
